,Recommended,402130,34272492,Posted: 16 August,all,Fineas,"I have been waiting out for this game, because it had received (when looking at the Steam reviews) a bunch of backlash ranging from inept game mechanics, poor optimisation and bugs.Now yesterday we wanted to play Flat Out 2, our number 1 party game on the lan party we are at and found the current networking setup do not support the features needed for lan play and because Game Spy is dead for a long time, there is no way here for us to play it.I was pleasantly surprised to see Flat Out 4 (or Fl4t Out as they try to brand it) costs only a ~11 euro. So I dived in, and was pleasantly surprised.Personally I do NOT bare a deep rooted hatred toward the other Flat Out games that “are not from Bugbear”, I simply did not like them. I was hoping to find some more variation by adding those games to my scope of racing party games, but they just felt lacking.THIS GAME. On this machine has everything I enjoy about a race game and darn well delivers on what I need from a party game (install, join and have fun).  Graphics look nice and smooth, run at +100 fps on my Ryzen 7, 1700X and MSI GTX 1070. I perceive no annoying stuttering and although things in the distance do not look as nice as near, I think it just looks just as good as or even better then Dirt 3 (which I will use as my drop-in-drop-out race game at the moment).Cars physics keep the cars on the road, steering feels direct, surfaces have a direct impact on car handling, but never it feel so slippery that I totally lose control. Which what I expect from an arcade racer. Smashing through things feels satisfying and keeps me finding a balance between the slowdowns caused by some destructible and nitro they yield or just going flat out (literally full throttle to the finish ignoring most or all obstacles).Soundtrack is descent, it’s the kind of punk bands you would expect in this time of game and are nice. My only grippe is that the same song starts after finishing every race when returning back to the menu.However THE MAIN SELLING POINT for me, is if it can satisfy the fun factor. Simply, is this game fun?Absolutely a full mouthed YES. We only played for 2 hours with some race and derby games and have been laughing and smiling teeth to teeth constantly. The ice cream truck specifically has literally burned its impression on us as the new sound of death. The ramping of a jet engine combined with the tune of the horn (playing a jolly ‘everybody sings this song’), closely followed by a power hit, an explosion, lots of smoke and wondering just what the hell happened. As they guy next to you continues their ice glazed path of destruction. We recorded the tune to induce PTSD among each other, by playing it on our phones when we walk by :-)Yes, YES, YES this is A, maybe not THE, but A worthy successor to one of our most favourite party games. It is different and not without some scrutiny. But overall, this game is worth at least twice its 11 euro price tag it has now. For it to be worth they full ~40 euro. I would expect: more crazy stunt levels, a bunch more colours for all the cars and in time a DLC for more tracks.A word for the developers: I feel sorry the community has burned your game to the ground. Because for us, this game a whole lot of fun and well worth our time and money.Take care, game on."
