76561197999782420,Recommended,402130,31096423,Posted: 12 April,all,MordaRazgrom,"I picked this game up on a whim and have been pleasantly surprised at just how much fun I have been having with it.  I highly recommend this game, as it is fun.Originally, my intent was to get some driving games to use my shiny new racing wheel and pedal accessory.  The steering wheel works well-enough in this game, but a controller is, honestly, a better fit, withthe exception that I still prefer to use my racing wheel and pedals on Time Trials.I have never played any other Flatout titles, so I cannot compare, but I am not biased either.I have come to view this game as a more realistic and more grown-up version of a certain Kart game that involves plumbers, anthropomorphic turtles, and gluttonous dinosaurs.You race in your car through various tracks, complete cups, unlock further cups and higher difficulty levels, and there is even a mode that gives you various offensive tools you can use against your opponents, which I thoroughly enjoy.The other racers are all distinct, and, after playing and racing against them a while, I have noticed that they have certain tendencies, which is pretty cool.  Some of them are focused on speed and being in front, and will usually compete with you heavily on the Fastest Lap Time, others are aggressive bulldozers and will do their best to knock you silly.  Some are insanely reckless, you will see them stomping their Nitro hard and then will, invariably, see them spinning through the air in a spectacular crash, while some are much more careful and you can actually learn from them by following them and seeing how they handle the trickier parts of the track.The tracks are also fantastic!  There is not a hige number of them, but you will race them forward and backward.  While that may seem insignificant, it does make a great difference and will absolutely make it a completely new track for you.  Each track has varied paths throught it, some are the shortest, some are the least cluttered, and you must be quick to decide whether you want to take a shortcut and gamble on your driving abilities, or go to a path apart from other racers to build up some momentum.The physics really impress me.  The crashes feel meaty and if you mess up and slam into the wall you will definitely feel it.  Hitting other cars is also satisfying, especially if it is the jerk that has constantly slammed into you on a previous run and caused you to go from first to tenth due to a spin out or slamming into the wall.  The different conditions require adjustment too, driving through mud on a rainy day is vastly different than driving it without the rain, which is where the different vehicles come into play.There are quite a few vehicles to buy and upgrade in career mode.  You can have volkswagen beetle like buggies, pickup trucks, caddilacs, jeeps and others.  Each one has its own strengths and weaknesses.  The pickup truck is very good at taking punishment, has a decent top speed and is generally rather stable, however it is slow on acceleration and its inertia may work against you from time to time as you slam headfirst into a pile of rocks.  The Jeep is my nemesis, I appreciate that is it a very fast, stable, and overall great car, but it is tiny and overturns at a stiff breeze, it is definitely a car for a much more skilled driver than I.There are many different game modes, from career, which will have you race, do destruction derby, and time trials, to Flatout Mode which assigns you a car and gives you a specific ruleset.  Either do a stunt, such as flinging your driver out the windshield into a baseball bat, or drive fast to try to prolong the inevitability of exploding, or Carnage mode which is a ""race"" technically, but you are gauged on how much chaos you cause to scenery and other drivers, with your position in the race serving only as a multiplier to your points.  Destroying a fence when first will get you many more points than when twelfth.Overall, this game is amazing, I wish more was done by marketing to get the word out, because this game is incredibly fun.p.S.  I cannot comment on multiplayer as I do not have much interest in it myself, but the prospect is an intriguing one and I will definitely give it a whirl one day.UPDATE:  i have recently switched over to playing the game exclusively with steering wheel and pedals, and the experience is even better now.  I can confirm that this game works very well with a racing wheel and pedals."
